!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

flush /flʌʃ/

(flushing,flushed,flushes) 

1. V-I If you flush , your face gets red because you are hot or ill, or because you are feeling a strong emotion such as embarrassment or anger. 脸红 

例： Do you sweat a lot or flush a lot? 你常出汗或是常脸红吗？ 

2. N-COUNT Flush is also a noun. 脸红 

例： There was a slight flush on his cheeks. 他的面颊上有淡淡的红晕。 

3. flushed ADJ 脸红的 

例： Her face was flushed with anger. 她气得满脸通红。 

4. V-T/V-I When someone flushes a toilet after using it, they fill the toilet bowl with water in order to clean it, usually by pressing a handle or pulling a chain. You can also say that a toilet flushes . 冲 (马桶) 

例： She flushed the toilet and went back in the bedroom. 她冲了马桶，然后回到卧室。 

5. N-COUNT Flush is also a noun. 冲水 

例： He heard the flush of a toilet. 他听到马桶的冲水声。 

6. V-T If you flush something down the toilet, you get rid of it by putting it into the toilet bowl and flushing the toilet. (从马桶里) 冲掉 

例： He was found trying to flush the pills down the toilet. 他被发现试图从马桶冲掉药丸。 

7. V-T If you flush a part of your body, you clean it or make it healthier by using a large amount of liquid to get rid of dirt or harmful substances. 冲洗 (身体某部位) 

例： Flush the eye with clean cold water for at least 15 minutes. 用干净的冷水冲洗眼睛至少15分钟。 

8. PHRASAL VERB Flush out means the same as . flush out同flush 

例： ...an 'alternative' therapy that gently flushes out the colon to remove toxins. …通过温和冲洗大肠排毒的一种“替代”疗法。 

9. V-T If you flush dirt or a harmful substance out of a place, you get rid of it by using a large amount of liquid. 冲洗 

例： That won't flush out all the sewage, but it should unclog some stinking drains. 那样做不会冲走全部的污水，但应该能疏通一下发臭的下水道。 

10. V-T If you flush people or animals out of a place where they are hiding, you find or capture them by forcing them to come out of that place. 把…赶出 

例： They flushed them out of their hiding places. 他们将其赶出藏身之地。 

11. ADJ level or even with another surface (与另一平面)平齐的 

12. ADV so as to be level or even 平齐地 

13. ADJ having plenty of money 富裕的 [非正式] 

14. V to cause (surfaces) to be on the same level or in the same plane 使在同一水平面上 

15. N a period of fresh growth of leaves, shoots, etc (树叶或幼苗等)破土而出的时期 

16. N (in poker and similar games) a hand containing only one suit (扑克牌等游戏中的)一手同花牌

